name: Etrian Odyssey Untold: The Millennium Girl
summary:
Etrian Odyssey Untold: The Millennium Girl is the first in the Untold series which are to be remakes of the original Etrian Odyssey games. The games are first person RPG dungeon crawlers where you create a map of the labyrinth as you explore and complete quests.

The game features two game modes. The new story mode, has a pre-made party with a more in-depth story that has voice acting and animated cutscenes, and an enhanced classic mode, customize a party of 5 from 9 classes to explore the Yggdrasil labyrinth.

The game allows for the save data from story mode to be carried over to the classic mode once completed.

esrb.synopsis: This is a role-playing game in which players control a group of adventurers that explore labyrinths to complete quests. As players traverse dungeons, they engage in turn-based combat against a variety of human enemies and fantasy creatures (e.g., large insects, slime creatures). Players select moves/attacks from a menu-screen of options; attacks are accompanied by light effects, mild explosions, and realistic gunfire. During the course of the game, some female characters wear revealing outfits that expose some cleavage and portions of buttocks. A dominatrix-themed character has attacks that are suggestively named (e.g., Cuffs, Gag, Ecstasy, and Climax). The game includes references to tobacco (e.g., a mission requiring players to obtain an item called “Pipe Tobacco”), as well as use and references to alcohol (e.g., a character holding a mug of beer; a woman whose cheeks appear red after drinking; a patron called "One-Armed drunkard"). The words “a*s,” “damn,” and “hell” can be heard in dialogue.
